## Environment Variables

The following environment variables can be used to configure the provider:

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `ARM_CLIENT_ID` | The client ID for service principal authentication (also accepted: `AZURE_CLIENT_ID`) |
| `ARM_CLIENT_SECRET` | The client secret for service principal authentication (also accepted: `AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET`) |
| `ARM_TENANT_ID` | The Azure AD tenant ID (also accepted: `AZURE_TENANT_ID`) |
| `ARM_ENVIRONMENT` | The Azure cloud environment (`public`, `usgovernment`, `china`) (also accepted: `AZURE_ENVIRONMENT`) |
| `AZURE_FEDERATED_TOKEN_FILE` | Path to federated token file (for workload identity) |
| `AZURE_AUTHORITY_HOST` | Azure AD authority host URL |
| `AZURE_CLIENT_ASSERTION` | Client assertion for federated identity credentials |

